snippet.textDisplay:
I can explain all of these results, easily.

Microwaves cause the electrons in metal to oscillate. If there is a means to a complete circuit, this causes an electrical flow, which can cause sparking.

If you notice, every time it sparks, there is a configuration that has a complete circuit (through the gap in which the sparks occur). When there are no sparks, the configuration doesn't allow a complete circuit.
